<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-07T11:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-07T11:36:00-05:00" n="580" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d580">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/554: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-07T10:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            7, 1919, 10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 9.55 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>3213. Senate petroleum bill was defeated in the Senate yesterday by
                                vote of 26 to 17. Senate will begin discussion of Executive
                                petroleum bill<note n="96" xml:id="d580fn96"><ref target="frus1918#pg_772"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                            Relations</hi>, 1918, p. 772</ref>.</note> today.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>